  "text": "We are interested in understanding how the system responds to the bankruptcy of a single bank, and in particular when this results in contagion events in which a finite fraction of the banks are shut down. In [CITATION_1] , generating functions techniques are exploited to give an analytical solution to the problem, and results from numerical simulations are presented as well. The main results of [CITATION_2] that are going to be relevant for this paper are the following (see figure 1 ):",
